## Architecture

This project follows **Clean Architecture** with strict layering. The **Dependency Rule**
is the fundamental invariant: source-code dependencies always point **inward**, never
from core toward frameworks/infrastructure.

### Layer Diagram

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Presentation (API routes, CLI, web)     │  ← Framework-specific entry points
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Application (services, commands, DTOs) │  ← Orchestration, use cases
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Core (entities, value objects, events) │  ← Pure domain, ZERO framework imports
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Infrastructure (DB, cache, HTTP, email)│  ← External integration implementations
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Mapping to Clean Architecture Circles

| Clean Architecture Circle | Project Layer | Directory |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Entities | Core | `core/` |
| Use Cases | Application | `application/` |
| Interface Adapters (inbound) | Presentation | `presentation/` |
| Frameworks & Drivers (outbound) | Infrastructure | `infrastructure/` |

### The Dependency Rule

**Always inward**: `presentation/infrastructure → application → core`

| Layer | May Import From | NEVER Imports From |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **core/** | stdlib, utils/ | application/, infrastructure/, presentation/, config/, ai/ |
| **application/** | core/ (protocols + base classes), ai/ (vertical), utils/ | infrastructure/, presentation/, config/ |
| **infrastructure/** | core/ (protocols), application/ (DTOs, mappers), utils/, libs | presentation/, ai/ |
| **presentation/** | application/ (services, DTOs), core/ (exceptions, enums, constants, interfaces), config/, utils/, ai/ | infrastructure/ (use DI) |
| **config/** | core/enums/ (Environment), utils/, external libs | application/, infrastructure/, presentation/, ai/ |
{%- if use_ai %}
| **ai/** | core/, application/, utils/, external AI libs | presentation/, config/, infrastructure/ |
{%- endif %}
| **utils/** | stdlib ONLY | ALL other project layers |

### Concern Boundaries

| Concern | ONLY In |
| --- | --- |
| HTTP status codes, request/response | `presentation/api/` |
| CLI exit codes, terminal output | `presentation/cli/` |
| HTML rendering, form handling | `presentation/web/` |
| Business rules, domain invariants | `core/` |
| Use case orchestration, DTO mapping | `application/` |
| Database queries, ORM, SQL, sessions | `infrastructure/persistence/` |
| Cache get/set/delete | `infrastructure/cache/` |
| Event publish/subscribe | `infrastructure/messaging/` |
| Environment variables, settings | `config/settings.py` |
| Pure, framework-agnostic helpers | `utils/` |

### Entry Points & Dependency Injection

ALL entry points use factory functions — no global mutable state:

- `create_api_app() -> FastAPI` in `presentation/api/app.py`
- `create_web_app() -> FastAPI` in `presentation/web/app.py`
- `cli() -> click.Group` in `presentation/cli/app.py`
{%- if use_celery %}
- `create_celery_app() -> Celery` in `config/celery.py`
{%- endif %}

DI wiring:

- `composition/container.py` wires gateway/repository protocols to concrete
  implementations
- Constructor injection via typed parameters — no service locator, no global mutable
  state
- Routes NEVER instantiate dependencies — use `presentation/api/dependencies.py`
  with `Depends()`
- Application services inherit `BaseService`, depend on port protocols ONLY
- Application services access persistence via **UoW repository properties**
  (e.g. `uow.users`), NEVER by importing concrete infrastructure classes

### Domain Modeling Patterns

- Domain entities: inherit `Entity` with `@dataclass(slots=True)`
- Value objects: `@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)`
- Domain events: `@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)`
- Commands and queries: frozen dataclasses
- `DomainError` hierarchy: `NotFound`, `Conflict`, `Validation`, `Authorization`
- ORM: SQLAlchemy 2.0+ with `Mapped[]` + `mapped_column()`, single async session factory

### Architecture Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)

- NO business logic in infrastructure, presentation, or middleware
- NO ORM models in core — core uses pure dataclasses (`frozen=True`, `slots=True`)
- NO Pydantic models in core — Pydantic is a port/adapter concern
- NO circular dependencies between any modules
- NO relative imports except within `__init__.py`
- NO `print()` — use `structlog` or `logging`
- NO `Any` type — use proper generics or `object`
- NO mutable default arguments
- NO `assert` for runtime validation
- NO `eval()`, `exec()`, `__import__()`, or `pickle.loads()` on untrusted input
- NO f-strings in logging calls — use `%s` formatting

