## Multi-Agent System

This project ships with a **coordinator / worker** multi-agent architecture for
**GitHub Copilot** (VS Code agent mode){% if with_gsd %} and **GSD-2** (CLI agent){% endif %}.
Agents are specialized by concern, use scoped tool permissions, and support handoffs
for human-approved stage transitions.

### Architecture Overview

```text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                         Human Developer                              │
│           (invokes coordinator or standalone agents)                  │
└─────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                          │
             ┌────────────▼────────────┐
             │      Coordinator        │  ← Central orchestrator
             │  (planning, impl,       │    End-to-end workflow
             │   review, test, docs)   │    with inlined phases
             └────┬───────┬───────┬────┘
                  │       │       │
         ┌────────┤       │       ├────────┐
         ▼        ▼       ▼       ▼        ▼
    ┌────────┐ ┌─────┐ ┌──────┐ ┌──────┐ ┌───────────────┐
    │  TDD   │ │Debug│ │Deep  │ │Review│ │Security Audit │
    │(R/W)   │ │(R/W)│ │Think.│ │(R/O) │ │(R/O, internal)│
    └────────┘ └─────┘ │(R/W) │ └──────┘ └───────────────┘
                       └──────┘
```

### GitHub Copilot Custom Instructions

The main custom instructions file (`.github/copilot-instructions.md`) applies to ALL
files (`applyTo: "**"`) and covers:

- Agent skills references (`.github/skills/`)
- Scoped instructions index (`.github/instructions/`)
- PEP 20 (Zen of Python) principles
- Clean Architecture layer rules and dependency direction
- File naming conventions (`.py`, `.zsh`, `.azcli`, `.jinja`)
- Python coding standards (type hints, constants, enums, `@final`, `@override`,
  logging, exceptions, keyword-only args, docstrings, visibility, naming)
- Frontend conventions (TypeScript, Vite, Bun, Biome, Tailwind v4)
- Shell conventions (zsh, `.azcli` for Azure CLI)
- Naming registry workflow
- Testing standards (pytest, hypothesis, vitest)
{%- if use_redis %}
- Redis caching conventions
{%- endif %}
{%- if database_backend != 'none' %}
- Database patterns (SQLAlchemy 2.0+, Alembic, indices, timestamps)
{%- endif %}
- Pydantic model configuration (`ConfigDict`, `Annotated`, `Field`)

