### GitHub Copilot Agents

Located in `.github/agents/`. Invoked via `@AgentName` in Copilot Chat (agent mode).

| Agent | File | Invocable | Tools | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Coordinator** | `coordinator.agent.md` | Yes | agent, read, search, edit, execute, web, context7 | Central orchestrator with inlined phase guidance (planning, implementation, review, testing, documentation); delegates to Security Auditor via handoff |
| **TDD** | `tdd.agent.md` | Yes | read, search, edit, execute, context7 | Red-Green-Refactor TDD orchestrator — fully self-contained, no subagent delegation |
| **Thorough Reviewer** | `thorough-reviewer.agent.md` | Yes | agent, read, search | Multi-perspective parallel code review (correctness, quality, security, architecture, performance) |
| **Deep Thinking** | `deep-thinking.agent.md` | Yes | read, search, edit, execute, web, context7 | Autonomous complex problem-solving with extended reasoning; persists until fully resolved |
| **Debug** | `debug.agent.md` | Yes | read, search, edit, execute, web, context7 | Systematic 4-phase debugging (gather context → reproduce → root cause → fix + verify) |
| **Security Auditor** | `security-auditor.agent.md` | No | read, search, web | OWASP/CWE vulnerability scanning — read-only, never modifies files; produces structured audit report |

### Copilot Handoff Workflow

The coordinator includes inlined phase guidance and supports **handoffs** — structured
transition points where the human can approve, redirect, or abort:

1. **Discovery** → handoff → **Planning** (architecture validation, task decomposition)
2. **Planning** → handoff → **Implementation** (coding standards, layer compliance)
3. **Implementation** → handoff → **Review** (quality assurance + security auditor)
4. **Review** → handoff → **Testing** (unit + integration + property tests)
5. **Testing** → handoff → **Documentation** (docstrings, CHANGELOG, docs/)

### Usage Examples

```
@Coordinator Implement a new user preferences feature with API endpoint and frontend form
@TDD Add a discount calculation service using test-driven development
@Thorough-Reviewer Review the changes in the current branch
@Debug Investigate the intermittent database connection timeout
@Deep-Thinking Design the caching strategy for the recommendation engine
```
### Agent Design Principles

1. **Least privilege**: Workers get only the tools they need (read-only agents cannot
   edit)
2. **Single responsibility**: Each agent has one clear concern
3. **Structured output**: Agents produce consistent, parseable formats
4. **Handoff gates**: Human stays in the loop at critical transitions
5. **Model selection**: Use the best available model from your provider;
   reasoning-heavy tasks benefit from stronger models
6. **Temperature tuning**: Read-only analysis at 0.1; code generation at 0.2-0.3
7. **Convention enforcement**: All agents reference this file and project conventions

