## MCP Servers

MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers provide tools that agents can invoke.

**GitHub Copilot**: MCP tools are referenced in agent `.agent.md` tool lists
(e.g., `context7/get-library-docs`, `context7/resolve-library-id`). Server extensions
are installed via workspace recommendations.
{% if with_gsd %}
**GSD-2**: MCP servers are configured in `.gsd/mcp.json`.
{% endif %}
| Server | Type | Source | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Context7** | http | `https://mcp.context7.com/mcp` | Up-to-date library/framework documentation |
| **GitHub** | http | Copilot built-in | GitHub issues, pull requests, repos, and code search |{% if use_playwright %}
| **Playwright** | stdio (npx) | `@playwright/mcp` | Browser automation for E2E web testing |{% endif %}{% if cloud_provider == 'azure' %}
| **Azure** | http | Copilot built-in | Azure resource management, deployments, monitoring |{% endif %}

### Usage

Agents with `context7/*` tools can resolve library IDs and fetch docs:

```
@Coordinator Use context7 to look up the latest FastAPI dependency injection patterns
```

The GitHub MCP server provides repository context:

```
@Coordinator List open issues labelled "bug" in this repo
```

