## Agent Skills

Agent skills provide domain knowledge that agents reference automatically. Each skill
is a directory containing a `SKILL.md` file following the
[Agent Skills standard](https://agentskills.io/). Skills can also be invoked as slash
commands.

Skills are stored in two locations for cross-agent compatibility:

- `.github/skills/` — GitHub Copilot (VS Code) reads skills from here
- `~/.agents/skills/` — GSD, Claude Code, and industry-standard agents resolve bare
  skill names from this global directory

| Skill | Directory | Scope | Key Rules |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Clean Architecture** | `clean-architecture/` | Layer boundaries, dependency rules | Dependency direction, protocol placement, DI wiring |
| **Python Conventions** | `python-conventions/` | Naming, typing, async patterns | Type hints, structured logging, keyword-only args |
| **Testing Conventions** | `testing-conventions/` | Pytest structure, coverage | Markers, factories, fixtures, >= 80% coverage |
| **Naming Registry** | `naming-registry/` | Registry-first constants | Edit JSON → validate → generate → check → test |

The `clean-architecture` skill is **MANDATORY** for all backend Python work — agents
MUST apply it regardless of task scope.

